    "name": "Kemet Public API",
    "description": "Professional Postman collection for the **Kemet** heavy machinery public REST API (Laravel 12).\n\n## Base URL\n`{{base_url}}` — default: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api`\n\n## Authentication\nNo authentication required. All endpoints are public.\n\n## Localization\nSupported locales: `en`, `ar`, `fr`, `es`, `ru`\n\nSet locale via:\n- Header: `X-Locale: en`\n- Query param: `?lang=en`\n\n## Response Envelope\nAll responses follow this structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": 200,\n  \"message\": \"Human-readable status message\",\n  \"data\": {},\n  \"pagination\": {}\n}\n```\n\n`pagination` is only included on paginated endpoints (FAQ).\n\n## Error Codes\n| Code | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 200 | Success |\n| 201 | Created (contact, consultation) |\n| 404 | Resource not found |\n| 422 | Validation error — `data` contains field errors |\n| 500 | Server error |\n\n## Setup\n1. Import `Kemet-API.postman_collection.json`\n2. Import `Kemet-Local.postman_environment.json`\n3. Run `php artisan serve` and ensure DB is seeded: `php artisan migrate --seed`\n4. Select the **Kemet — Local** environment\n\nGenerated: 2026-06-11 12:09:19 UTC",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "43687726"
  },
